<appendix xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
  version="5.0">
  <title>Documentation quality</title>
  <para>Depending on the amount of time that is available, you can use the following framework to
    define the quality target for documentation.</para>
  <table>
    <title>&isg; quality parameters</title>
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <thead>
        <row>
          <entry>Quality parameter</entry>
          <entry>Fix?</entry>
        </row>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry>Typos</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Vernacular</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Spell out contractions</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Extraneous phrasal verbs</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Complicated language</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Serial commas</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Passive voice</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Dangling modifiers</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Complete sentences</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Consistent headers</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Extraneous ordered lists<footnote>
              <para>Often, it is tempting to use an ordered list in places where an unordered list
                is appropriate, such as a list of three platforms on which to install software.
                Leave it up to the reader to count, and in this example use an unordered
                list.</para>
            </footnote></entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry/>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry> </entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry> </entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </table>
